DETERM_REMARKS: It would be highly unusual to see all four of the listed fungi on a Prunus peel that is only 2cm square.  An identification of Colletotrichum would require the observation of conidiophores of this fungus, which are not present.  An identification of Fusicoccum would also require the observation of pycnidia and conidiogenous cells of this fungus, which are also not present.  No conidiophores of Fusarium, nor conidia of Fusarium were observed on the submitted slide.  Cladosporium is present.  Conidia and conidiogenous cells of Aureobasidium are present.
